You should only do mark-to-market operation; do not assume any strategy like cutting-loss, taking-profit etc., all the strategy is given externally, you ONLY do MARK TO MARKET. nothing more. you just need to do it well.

For now, it is only options (we will only use the data in data/synthetic_options.csv) AND EVERY OPTION IS EUROPEAN OPTION.

Input:
it will be a dataframe with columns [date, option_name, target_units], this is pre-given, and for simplicity, you can assume target_units is the fixed target unit for each trading day, I will not change the target units by any chance once given.

since we will only use the data in data/synthetic_options.csv, there won't be anything beyond that, so you can easily generate the metadata of those options (expiration, strike, call/put etc.)

Logic:
