f) you need to check if there is sufficient money to do the next day's trade, make it configurable, now for simplicity, default behavior is to assume we can borrow at 0 interest rate, so insufficient fund wont stop backtest

g) cash is sitting on 0 interest rate, no need to model interests.

Output:
you should have comprehensive output and simple output.

Simple output: time series of portfolio value everyday

Comprehensive output: detailed dataframe of each day's position, include for given date, what are the holdings, what are their bid/ask and current market value (assume we can liquidate right now, for long position we sell them, so mark at bid; for short position we buy back all, so mark at ask), and the aggregated transaction cost at each option level as well as portfolio level;
capital weights of each position at portfolio etc., you can add reasonable metrics to the output.

